The "Message is not sending" error occurs because the **Chat ID** (the destination address for the message) is missing. Even though you provided the Bot Token, the bot needs to know *who* to send the message to (your personal Telegram account).

Since you requested to **remove the input box**, I have implemented a smart **"One-Click Connect"** feature.

**How to fix it now:**
1.  Go to the **Feedback** tab in the app.
2.  You will see a "Connect Telegram" screen.
3.  Send `/start` to your bot on Telegram.
4.  Click the **"Connect"** button in the app.
5.  The app will automatically fetch your Chat ID and save it securely. Now you can send messages!

